{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "As part of the settlement, which came after more than seven years of litigation, the city agreed to pay nearly $100 million in back pay and benefits.", "abstract": "New York City Fire Department agrees to settle discrimination case and pay nearly $100 million in back pay and benefits to minorities whose efforts to join the department were thwarted by what courts have ruled were institutional biases; also agrees to create a chief of diversity and inclusion, who will report directly to the fire commissioner, as well as a diversity advocate who will monitor hiring practices and cadet training for discrimination.", "section_name": "N.Y. / Region", "print_page": "17", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Marc", "role": "reported", "lastname": "SANTORA", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}, {"firstname": "Michael", "role": "reported", "lastname": "SCHWIRTZ", "rank": 2, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MARC SANTORA and MICHAEL SCHWIRTZ", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/03/19/nyregion/new-york-settles-bias-lawsuit-against-fire-department.html", "lead_paragraph": "As part of the settlement, which came after more than seven years of litigation, the city agreed to pay nearly $100 million in back pay and benefits.", "headline": {"main": "New York City Settles Lawsuit Accusing Fire Dept. of Racial Bias", "print_headline": "City Settles Lawsuit Accusing Fire Dept. of Racial Bias"}, "_id": "5328815838f0d8036a98b93b", "word_count": "967", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/03/19/nyregion/VULCANsub/VULCAN-1395179922908-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/03/19/nyregion/VULCANsub/VULCAN-1395179922908-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 398, "url": "images/2014/03/19/nyregion/VULCANsub/VULCAN-1395179922908-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/03/19/nyregion/VULCANs